@startuml sequence_record_audit
title Sequence Diagram — Record Audit Entry

participant "AdrService\n(or any service)" as Caller
participant "AuditService" as Svc
participant "AuditEntryFactory" as Factory
participant "AuditRepository" as Repo
database "Couchbase\n(audit collection)" as CB

note over Caller : After completing a significant\naction (e.g., status change)

Caller -> Svc : record("status_changed", "adr",\nadrId, actorId,\n{ previousStatus: "draft",\n  newStatus: "in_review" })

Svc -> Factory : create("status_changed", "adr",\nadrId, actorId, details)
Factory -> Factory : Generate UUID\nCapture ISO 8601 timestamp
Factory --> Svc : AuditEntry {\n  type: "audit_entry",\n  action: "status_changed",\n  resourceType: "adr",\n  resourceId: adrId,\n  actorId: actorId,\n  timestamp: "2026-04-15T10:30:00Z",\n  details: { previousStatus, newStatus }\n}

Svc -> Repo : insert(auditEntry)
Repo -> CB : collection.insert(\n  "audit::2026-04-15T10:30:00Z::uuid",\n  auditEntry)
CB --> Repo : MutationResult
Repo --> Svc : AuditEntry

note over CB : Entry is now immutable.\nNo UPDATE or DELETE\npermissions on this collection.

Svc --> Caller : AuditEntry (confirmation)

@enduml
